=== Interpretation guide ===
  - Visual: open _compare_grid.png. Is B visibly similar to A?
  - If A ≈ B (same subject, similar detail/composition):
    → t2v at t_lat=1 produces image-quality output.
    → multi-frame code is the gap; bisect mask/positions/attention.
  - If B is washed/blurry/different even at t_lat=1:
    → video weights diverged from image weights OR t2v code
      at t_lat=1 already degrades (possible edge case).
    → strongly supports training-data answer.
